WEBVTT

00:00:19.417 --> 00:00:20.875
There's the exit!

00:00:39.167 --> 00:00:41.333
That took years off my life!

00:00:41.792 --> 00:00:44.125
But it saved time, right?

00:00:44.125 --> 00:00:45.958
Honestly...

00:01:02.292 --> 00:01:05.333
Where will the talks be taking place?

00:01:05.333 --> 00:01:06.417
Hmm...

00:01:07.125 --> 00:01:08.667
Let's see...

00:01:09.208 --> 00:01:11.583
To the northwest,
inside that mountain.

00:01:11.583 --> 00:01:14.167
--How much time do we have left?
--Twenty minutes.

00:01:14.542 --> 00:01:16.500
I hope we make it!

00:01:21.583 --> 00:01:27.042
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:01:27.042 --> 00:01:32.542
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:01:42.708 --> 00:01:53.042
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:01:53.167 --> 00:02:03.750
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:02:03.875 --> 00:02:09.125
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:02:09.125 --> 00:02:12.917
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:02:14.042 --> 00:02:19.292
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:02:19.417 --> 00:02:24.333
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:30.083
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:36.167
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:02:38.042 --> 00:02:44.542
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:02:50.083 --> 00:02:54.083
"General of the Blazing Flame"

00:02:56.583 --> 00:02:59.125
"ALfheim, Neutral Territory, Butterfly Valley"

00:02:59.458 --> 00:03:03.417
I don't know if we'll make it there
before the Salamanders.

00:03:03.417 --> 00:03:08.500
Yeah. Even if we can warn them,
we'll either barely get the leaders out,

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:11.292
or all die together in battle.

00:03:13.417 --> 00:03:17.792
Players detected. A group
of 68 players is ahead.

00:03:17.792 --> 00:03:21.125
That's probably the
Salamander attack force.

00:03:28.042 --> 00:03:30.458
Fourteen more are up ahead.

00:03:30.458 --> 00:03:34.042
Most likely the Sylph and
Cait Sith diplomats.

00:03:34.458 --> 00:03:37.750
Fifty seconds until they make contact.

00:03:38.792 --> 00:03:40.708
We didn't make it in time.

00:03:43.208 --> 00:03:46.333
Thank you, Kirito.
This is far enough.

00:03:46.583 --> 00:03:50.833
You go to the World Tree.
I'm going to save Sakuya.

00:03:51.667 --> 00:03:55.917
It wasn't for long, but it was fun.
I hope we meet again!

00:03:56.792 --> 00:04:00.417
Running away at this point
isn't really my style, so...

00:04:08.792 --> 00:04:10.583
Why are there Salamanders here?

00:04:35.708 --> 00:04:38.125
Everyone, sheathe your swords!

00:04:38.250 --> 00:04:39.625
Who's that?

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:42.083
Sakuya!

00:04:42.750 --> 00:04:47.292
--Leafa... What are you doing here?
--It's not easy to explain.

00:04:47.292 --> 00:04:52.625
But the one thing I can say
is that our fates depend on him.

00:04:53.708 --> 00:04:55.583
What is going on?

00:04:55.958 --> 00:04:58.167
I want to talk to your commander!

00:05:06.958 --> 00:05:10.292
What's a Spriggan doing here?

00:05:13.375 --> 00:05:19.750
I'll kill you however you answer, but
in honor of your bravery, I'll hear you out.

00:05:19.917 --> 00:05:24.250
My name is Kirito, an ambassador
for the Spriggan-Undine alliance.

00:05:24.250 --> 00:05:30.042
Since you're attacking this place, I assume
you desire full-scale war with our four races.

00:05:35.458 --> 00:05:38.250
An Undine-Spriggan alliance?

00:05:38.750 --> 00:05:42.542
And you, without a single guard,
are their ambassador?

00:05:42.542 --> 00:05:48.708
Yes, that's right. I'm merely here to negotiate
trade terms with the Sylphs and Cait Siths.

00:05:48.708 --> 00:05:52.333
But if the talks are disrupted,
we won't stop there.

00:05:52.333 --> 00:05:56.750
The four races will likely ally
against the Salamanders.

00:05:58.417 --> 00:06:02.333
You're all alone, armed
with only mediocre gear.

00:06:02.333 --> 00:06:05.333
You can't expect me to believe you.

00:06:07.625 --> 00:06:13.208
If you withstand my assault for 30 seconds
I'll believe you're an ambassador.

00:06:13.375 --> 00:06:15.417
That's generous...

00:06:15.417 --> 00:06:16.917
This is bad.

00:06:17.750 --> 00:06:20.083
That Salamander's two-handed sword...

00:06:20.083 --> 00:06:25.333
It's the Demonic Sword Gram. I've heard you need
a two-handed sword skill of 950 to equip it.

00:06:25.333 --> 00:06:27.250
N-Nine hundred fifty?

00:06:27.250 --> 00:06:33.250
Yes. If he's using it, he must be
General Eugene. Do you know him?

00:06:33.250 --> 00:06:35.458
I-I know the name.

00:06:35.750 --> 00:06:38.708
Younger brother of the
Salamander leader, Mortimer.

00:06:38.708 --> 00:06:43.500
I've heard they're brothers in real life.
The elder is a strategist. The younger, a soldier.

00:06:43.500 --> 00:06:48.083
In terms of sheer power, he's said
to be the game's strongest player!

00:06:48.083 --> 00:06:50.833
The game's strongest player...

00:06:52.167 --> 00:06:53.500
Kirito...

00:07:11.792 --> 00:07:12.958
What was that?

00:07:13.083 --> 00:07:17.625
The Demonic Sword Gram has a bonus skill,
Ethereal Shift, letting it phase

00:07:17.625 --> 00:07:21.375
when someone tries to block
with a shield or sword.

00:07:21.375 --> 00:07:23.000
That's insane!

00:07:24.958 --> 00:07:27.167
I'm amazed you're still alive.

00:07:27.167 --> 00:07:29.958
What was that attack?

00:07:43.208 --> 00:07:44.583
That hurts...

00:07:45.083 --> 00:07:48.250
Hey, hasn't it been 30 seconds yet?

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:53.583
Sorry, but I've decided to kill you.
Now you have to survive until I do.

00:07:53.583 --> 00:07:55.625
Damn it...

00:07:55.625 --> 00:07:57.083
I'll show you!

00:08:00.375 --> 00:08:06.583
This will be tough. They're equally skilled,
but Eugene's weapon is far superior.

00:08:06.750 --> 00:08:08.125
Even so...

00:08:09.708 --> 00:08:11.958
Even so, Kirito will...

00:08:37.750 --> 00:08:38.917
What?

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:41.750
Let me borrow this.

00:08:42.417 --> 00:08:43.917
K-Kirito?

00:08:47.125 --> 00:08:50.083
Was that meant to buy you time?

00:08:56.208 --> 00:08:57.583
He's gone?

00:08:58.667 --> 00:09:00.583
Did he run away?

00:09:00.583 --> 00:09:02.292
Of course not!

00:09:04.875 --> 00:09:10.500
As long as I'm alive, I won't
let any party members die.

00:09:13.625 --> 00:09:16.542
<i>Kirito would never run.</i>

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:26.292
Kirito!

00:09:52.083 --> 00:09:53.750
Die!

00:10:32.375 --> 00:10:36.125
--Splendid! Simply splendid!
--Wow, nice fight!

00:10:36.125 --> 00:10:37.958
Hurrah!

00:10:39.542 --> 00:10:40.958
Not bad!

00:10:40.958 --> 00:10:42.792
I'm speechless!

00:11:19.917 --> 00:11:21.917
You have some brilliant skills.

00:11:21.917 --> 00:11:25.958
You're the most powerful
player that I've ever seen.

00:11:25.958 --> 00:11:27.542
Hey, thanks.

00:11:27.750 --> 00:11:33.125
To think someone like you was among the
Spriggans. The world's bigger than I thought.

00:11:33.125 --> 00:11:35.958
Will you believe me then?

00:11:46.292 --> 00:11:48.083
Gene, a word?

00:11:48.708 --> 00:11:50.542
Kagemune? What is it?

00:11:50.542 --> 00:11:52.500
That guy...

00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:56.292
I'd prefer not to fight you one-on-one.

00:11:57.167 --> 00:12:01.375
You know that my party was
wiped out yesterday, right?

00:12:01.375 --> 00:12:02.458
Yes.

00:12:02.458 --> 00:12:06.250
This is the very Spriggan who did it.

00:12:06.958 --> 00:12:09.625
There was indeed an Undine with him.

00:12:14.667 --> 00:12:16.042
Very well.

00:12:16.917 --> 00:12:19.208
Then I suppose I must believe it.

00:12:19.417 --> 00:12:25.625
It's true that neither I nor our leader
intends to fight the Undines and Spriggans.

00:12:26.417 --> 00:12:28.125
We'll withdraw for now.

00:12:28.417 --> 00:12:31.375
But someday, I'll fight you again.

00:12:31.375 --> 00:12:33.000
Sounds good to me.

00:12:37.167 --> 00:12:40.958
So there are some Salamanders
who can be reasonable!

00:12:40.958 --> 00:12:43.708
You're really insane,
you know?

00:12:43.708 --> 00:12:45.792
I get that a lot.

00:12:47.458 --> 00:12:51.583
Excuse me, but could you
explain what's happening?

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:55.042
I see.

00:12:55.667 --> 00:13:00.958
I did sense some degree of irritation
lurking in Sigurd's attitude.

00:13:00.958 --> 00:13:03.917
Irritation? At what?

00:13:04.167 --> 00:13:07.875
Most likely, he couldn't accept that,

00:13:07.875 --> 00:13:12.500
in terms of power, we were falling
behind the Salamanders.

00:13:13.125 --> 00:13:16.208
Sigurd's a man to whom
power is important.

00:13:16.333 --> 00:13:19.625
Not just for his character
stats and abilities,

00:13:19.625 --> 00:13:22.708
he also keenly desires
power as a player.

00:13:23.292 --> 00:13:27.375
But even so, why would he
spy for the Salamanders?

00:13:27.375 --> 00:13:32.583
You've heard about the 5.0 update
they'll be releasing soon?

00:13:32.583 --> 00:13:36.042
Apparently, they're finally putting
in a reincarnation system.

00:13:36.875 --> 00:13:40.250
--Then...
--Mortimer put him up to it.

00:13:40.417 --> 00:13:45.292
"Bring us the head of your leader, and we'll
allow you to reincarnate as a Salamander."

00:13:45.792 --> 00:13:49.000
So what will you do, Sakuya?

00:13:53.083 --> 00:13:56.375
Rue, you've raised your
dark-magic skill, right?

00:13:56.375 --> 00:13:57.625
Yes.

00:13:57.625 --> 00:14:00.417
Open a Moonlight Mirror to Sigurd.

00:14:08.292 --> 00:14:09.333
Sigurd.

00:14:10.333 --> 00:14:11.750
S-Sakuya?

00:14:11.750 --> 00:14:15.083
Indeed. Unfortunately, I'm still alive.

00:14:15.083 --> 00:14:18.708
Why? I mean, how was the meeting?

00:14:18.708 --> 00:14:23.208
It concluded successfully.
We must still sign the treaty though.

00:14:24.125 --> 00:14:27.250
Oh, right... We had
an unexpected guest.

00:14:27.250 --> 00:14:28.875
A g-guest?

00:14:29.458 --> 00:14:32.750
General Eugene sends his regards.

00:14:36.042 --> 00:14:37.375
Leafa...

00:14:37.708 --> 00:14:38.917
So that's it!

00:14:38.917 --> 00:14:41.542
Those incompetent lizards.

00:14:42.167 --> 00:14:43.417
Well?

00:14:43.417 --> 00:14:49.333
What will you do, Sakuya? Fine me?
Or kick me out of the government?

00:14:49.333 --> 00:14:54.292
But without me running the military,
how long will your rule last?

00:14:54.292 --> 00:15:00.333
No, if you cannot stand being a Sylph,
I thought I would grant your request.

00:15:00.333 --> 00:15:01.625
Wh-What?

00:15:05.958 --> 00:15:07.875
Are you insane?

00:15:07.875 --> 00:15:11.500
"Your leader has stripped you of your rights as
a Sylph and banished you from your territory."
Me? You're banishing me?

00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:15.458
That's right. You can wander
the neutral territory as a renegade.

00:15:15.458 --> 00:15:19.458
I pray you will find something
new there to occupy your time.

00:15:21.292 --> 00:15:22.833
Curse you...

00:15:37.542 --> 00:15:38.708
Sakuya?

00:15:38.708 --> 00:15:40.667
I thank you, Leafa.

00:15:40.667 --> 00:15:43.667
I'm very happy you came to save me.

00:15:43.833 --> 00:15:46.167
I didn't do anything.

00:15:46.167 --> 00:15:48.458
You should thank Kirito.

00:15:48.458 --> 00:15:51.250
That's true. Just who are you?

00:15:51.792 --> 00:15:55.875
Hey, what you were saying about being
a Spriggan-Undine ambassador...

00:15:56.042 --> 00:15:57.417
Is that true?

00:16:03.375 --> 00:16:07.917
Oh, that was just a big lie.
A bluff, a con, a negotiation.

00:16:08.833 --> 00:16:13.500
What a crazy man. To fabricate
that under those circumstances.

00:16:13.667 --> 00:16:18.125
Whenever I have a bad hand,
I always raise the pot.

00:16:18.125 --> 00:16:21.833
For a big liar, you're pretty strong.

00:16:21.833 --> 00:16:25.542
Maybe you're the Spriggans' secret weapon?

00:16:25.542 --> 00:16:29.542
Of course not. I'm just a
humble wandering bodyguard.

00:16:33.250 --> 00:16:37.458
If you aren't tied down, why not
be a mercenary for the Cait Sith?

00:16:37.458 --> 00:16:40.458
You'll get three meals a day,
plus snacks and a nap.

00:16:41.125 --> 00:16:44.417
Kirito, was it? What do you say?

00:16:44.417 --> 00:16:49.667
Since I've taken a personal interest in you,
how about a drink later in Sylvain, as thanks?

00:16:49.833 --> 00:16:50.750
Wait...

00:16:50.750 --> 00:16:53.792
That's not fair, Sakuya!

00:16:54.167 --> 00:16:56.750
No seducing!

00:16:56.917 --> 00:17:01.000
Who are you to talk?
You're clinging to him too much.

00:17:04.500 --> 00:17:06.042
Stop it.

00:17:06.042 --> 00:17:07.917
Kirito is my...

00:17:09.958 --> 00:17:11.417
My...

00:17:15.083 --> 00:17:18.583
Um, m-my...

00:17:23.375 --> 00:17:26.208
I appreciate the offer.

00:17:26.208 --> 00:17:31.917
But I'm sorry. She promised
to take me to the World Tree.

00:17:31.917 --> 00:17:35.667
Oh? I see. That's a shame.

00:17:35.667 --> 00:17:38.667
You're going to Arun, Leafa?
Sightseeing?

00:17:39.417 --> 00:17:40.708
Or...

00:17:40.958 --> 00:17:45.000
I was planning to leave the Sylphs...

00:17:45.000 --> 00:17:49.458
But now I'm going to return to Sylvain,
although I'm not sure when.

00:17:49.458 --> 00:17:51.500
Understood. I'm relieved.

00:17:51.500 --> 00:17:54.667
Make sure you come back.
Bring him with you.

00:17:54.667 --> 00:17:58.500
Stop at my place on the way back.
We'll throw you a party.

00:18:02.750 --> 00:18:06.875
Thank you so much for
coming today, Leafa and Kirito.

00:18:07.333 --> 00:18:12.750
Had we fallen, the disparity with the Salamanders
would have become insurmountable.

00:18:12.750 --> 00:18:16.583
--I'd like to thank you somehow.
--No, it was nothing.

00:18:16.583 --> 00:18:22.000
Hey, Sakuya... Alicia. Wasn't the goal
of this alliance to venture up the World Tree?

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:25.375
"World Tree" "Cait Sith Territory - Capital Freelia"
"Sylph Territory - Capital Sylvain"
Yes, ultimately.

00:18:25.375 --> 00:18:29.125
"World Tree" "Cait Sith Territory - Capital Freelia"
"Sylph Territory - Capital Sylvain"
I want you to let us accompany you.

00:18:29.125 --> 00:18:31.458
"World Tree" "Cait Sith Territory - Capital Freelia"
"Sylph Territory - Capital Sylvain"
And as soon as possible.

00:18:35.333 --> 00:18:40.667
I have no objection.
Rather, we'd love to ask you to do so.

00:18:40.667 --> 00:18:43.375
But why are you in such a hurry?

00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:51.208
I came to this world to reach
the top of the World Tree,

00:18:51.458 --> 00:18:54.833
in order to meet someone
who may be there.

00:18:55.833 --> 00:18:58.125
The Fairy King Oberon?

00:18:58.125 --> 00:19:00.542
No... I don't think so.

00:19:01.542 --> 00:19:04.583
It's someone I can't reach
in the real world,

00:19:05.083 --> 00:19:07.542
but I have to see, no matter what.

00:19:07.875 --> 00:19:13.708
However, it will probably take time
to prepare all the raid members' equipment.

00:19:13.958 --> 00:19:16.375
More than just a day or two...

00:19:16.375 --> 00:19:17.667
I see...

00:19:18.583 --> 00:19:20.042
That's true.

00:19:20.042 --> 00:19:26.500
For now, since my only goal is to reach
the base of the tree, we'll work out the rest ourselves.

00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:27.917
Oh, right.

00:19:29.917 --> 00:19:33.083
If you want, you can
add this to your war chest.

00:19:38.625 --> 00:19:40.750
S-Sakuya! Look!

00:19:43.208 --> 00:19:46.500
All these 100,000-Yuld mithril pieces!

00:19:46.750 --> 00:19:50.417
You're sure? This could
build a castle on prime land.

00:19:50.417 --> 00:19:53.417
I don't mind.
I don't need it anymore.

00:19:53.417 --> 00:19:57.917
This will get us really close
to the amount we need.

00:19:57.917 --> 00:20:02.958
We'll ready our equipment as quickly as we can.
And when we're set, we'll call you.

00:20:02.958 --> 00:20:04.250
Thank you.

00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:09.833
Thanks! See you soon!

00:20:15.417 --> 00:20:19.417
It kind of feels like none
of that really happened.

00:20:24.583 --> 00:20:26.292
Honestly...

00:20:26.292 --> 00:20:29.375
I told you no cheating, Daddy.

00:20:30.083 --> 00:20:32.167
Wh-What are you talking about?

00:20:32.167 --> 00:20:35.792
When those leaders were clinging
to you, your heart was pounding.

00:20:35.792 --> 00:20:39.000
W-Well, guys can't help it!

00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:40.250
Jeez.

00:20:40.250 --> 00:20:43.792
H-Hey, Yui, aren't I a problem?

00:20:44.375 --> 00:20:46.667
It looks like you're okay.

00:20:46.917 --> 00:20:48.167
Wh-Why?

00:20:51.833 --> 00:20:55.375
It doesn't really feel like you're a girl.

00:20:55.583 --> 00:20:57.167
Wait... Hey.

00:20:57.167 --> 00:20:59.458
What does that mean?

00:20:59.458 --> 00:21:04.083
I-I mean you're easy to get along with...
In a good way... Yeah.

00:21:04.250 --> 00:21:09.167
Never mind that! Let's get going
to Arun! Or the sun will set on us!

00:21:09.167 --> 00:21:11.708
Hey, wait!

00:21:37.417 --> 00:21:42.458
8-11-3-2-3-2-9.

00:21:47.042 --> 00:21:50.750
Kirito, I'll do my best, okay?

00:22:17.917 --> 00:22:25.042
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:22:25.042 --> 00:22:34.750
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:22:46.125 --> 00:22:52.875
<i>These endless feelings were</i>
<i>swallowed up into my daily life</i>

00:22:53.250 --> 00:23:00.083
<i>Swaying as they</i>
<i>change shape yet again</i>

00:23:00.458 --> 00:23:07.375
<i>Is it too late now? I ask</i>
<i>myself but receive no answer</i>

00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:15.042
<i>It's all up to me now,</i>
<i>both the ending and the beginning</i>

00:23:15.208 --> 00:23:22.167
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:23:22.167 --> 00:23:29.333
<i>I'm going to spread my wings</i>
<i>and head towards that gentle light</i>

00:23:29.333 --> 00:23:36.708
<i>Carrying the passion</i>
<i>I've lit in my heart</i>

00:23:36.708 --> 00:23:44.958
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:53.195
Next Time: "The Truth About ALfheim."
